article.headline: Long Island U. 71, Bethune-Cookman 46
article.story: EDS: APNewsNow. Long Island U. 71, Bethune-Cookman 46. NEW YORK -- Jaytornah Wisseh scored 14 points and Long Island University turned in one of its best defensive efforts in years in a 71-46 victory over Bethune-Cookman on Wednesday night. The Blackbirds (4-5) converted 17 turnovers by the Wildcats into 22 points and limited Bethune-Cookman (4-6) to 32.1 percent shooting from the field. It was the fewest points allowed by LIU since an 80-39 victory over CCNY on Dec. 22, 2005. The Blackbirds closed the first half on a 17-7 run that Wisseh capped with a long 3-pointer that made it 31-18. They opened the second half with a 9-4 run that gave LIU an 18-point lead. Ron Manigault had 11 points and nine rebounds for the Blackbirds, while Tyrone Mattison added 11 points in 18 minutes. Elliott Stanley had 12 points for the Wildcats, while leading scorer C.J. Reed was limited to five points on 2-of-16 shooting.
